                        <provenance><desc> The name of the first owner was <persName ref="PRS12580FessehaSeyon" role="owner"/>, son of <persName ref="PRS12581Anorewos"/>, for whose name have been substituted those of 
                            <persName ref="PRS12582WaldaAragawi"/> and <persName ref="PRS12583WaldaAragawi"/>.</desc>. The manuscript had very probably belonged to a church in the <placeName ref="LOC3577Gondar"/> area, 
                            from where it was taken by
                            <persName ref="PRS9430Tewodros"/> and brought to <placeName ref="INS0101MadhaneAlam"/>. It was then looted 
                            by the British <persName ref="PRS7484Napier">Napier</persName> expedition in <date>1868</date>.
                            The manuscript was then sent to the Royal Library at Windsor and 
                            presented by <persName ref="PRS9745Victoria"/> to the <placeName ref="INS00001BL"/> on the <date>21st January 1869</date>.
